Hello, the next task is to complete the marketplace backend using the infra api server.
We have already made a place for that and now we need the implemnetation.
In the .env and the values file.yaml (and thus in the deployment) we have the variable infraMarketplaceApiServer which contains the dns for the infra api server for chart deployment and undeployment (deletion).
First of all I want to change the variable from infraMarketplaceApiServer to infraChartsApiServer. Keep it in the same place under marketplace, just change the name in all the relevant places.

Please read the code to understand the structure and design of the relevant files (marketplace frontend and backend).
So here are the endpoints we need to call (when calling deploy / delete) depends if agent / mcp or dev / release.
So make sure to put all the relevant properties in the request.


Chart (agent / mcp) deployment

curl -X POST http://x.x.x.x:8000/api/infra/deploy \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
"entity_name": "my-test-app",
"entity_type": "agent",
"chart_name": "test-app",
"chart_version": "0.1.0",
"owner_username": "userA",
"target_environment": "dev",
}'


Chart (agent / mcp) deployment with values override.

curl -X POST http://x.x.x.x:8000/api/infra/deploy \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
"entity_name": "my-test-app",
"entity_type": "agent",
"chart_name": "test-app",
"chart_version": "0.1.0",
"owner_username": "userA",
"target_environment": "dev",
"values_override": {
"replicaCount": 3
}
}'


Chart (agent / mcp) deletion (undeployment).

curl -X POST http://x.x.x.x:8000/api/infra/delete \ 
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
"entity_name": "my-test-app",
"entity_type": "agent",
"owner_username": "userA",
"target_environment": "dev"
}'


